Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    set -e

    # Update package index and install Python & pip
    apt-get update
    DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip

    # Install pytest for the task’s automated grading
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Prepare initial filesystem state for the “credential rotation” task
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Ensure the directory tree /home/user/secrets exists
    mkdir -p /home/user/secrets

    # Create the retired credential file as an empty (zero-byte) file
    touch /home/user/secrets/old_credentials.txt
    truncate -s 0 /home/user/secrets/old_credentials.txt

    # Set sensible permissions (readable by any non-privileged user)
    chmod 644 /home/user/secrets/old_credentials.txt

    # Clean up APT caches to keep the image small
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

%environment
    chmod 755 /home/user

    # Keep a predictable PATH; do NOT override $HOME
    export PATH=/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin

%help
    Container for the “Log the SHA-256 signature of the retired credential file” task.
    It provides:
      • /home/user/secrets/old_credentials.txt  (zero-byte placeholder file)
      • Python 3 + pytest (needed for automated grading)
    The student must create /home/user/rotation/credential_rotation.log according to
    the task requirements.